4016 static void maybePrintCallAddrSpace(const Value *Operand, const Instruction *I,
4017  raw_ostream &Out) {
4018  // We print the address space of the call if it is non-zero.
4019  if (Operand == nullptr) {
4020  Out << " <cannot get addrspace!>";
4021  return;
4022  }
4023  unsigned CallAddrSpace = Operand->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
4024  bool PrintAddrSpace = CallAddrSpace != 0;
4025  if (!PrintAddrSpace) {
4026  const Module *Mod = getModuleFromVal(I);
4027  // We also print it if it is zero but not equal to the program address space
4028  // or if we can't find a valid Module* to make it possible to parse
4029  // the resulting file even without a datalayout string.
4030  if (!Mod || Mod->getDataLayout().getProgramAddressSpace() != 0)
4031  PrintAddrSpace = true;
4032  }
4033  if (PrintAddrSpace)
4034  Out << " addrspace(" << CallAddrSpace << ")";
4035 }
4036 
4037 // This member is called for each Instruction in a function..
4038 void AssemblyWriter::printInstruction(const Instruction &I) {
4039  if (AnnotationWriter) AnnotationWriter->emitInstructionAnnot(&I, Out);
4040 
4041  // Print out indentation for an instruction.
4042  Out << " ";
4043 
4044  // Print out name if it exists...
4045  if (I.hasName()) {
4046  PrintLLVMName(Out, &I);
4047  Out << " = ";
4048  } else if (!I.getType()->isVoidTy()) {
4049  // Print out the def slot taken.
4050  int SlotNum = Machine.getLocalSlot(&I);
4051  if (SlotNum == -1)
4052  Out << "<badref> = ";
4053  else
4054  Out << '%' << SlotNum << " = ";
4055  }
4056 
4057  if (const CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I)) {
4058  if (CI->isMustTailCall())
4059  Out << "musttail ";
4060  else if (CI->isTailCall())
4061  Out << "tail ";
4062  else if (CI->isNoTailCall())
4063  Out << "notail ";
4064  }
4065 
4066  // Print out the opcode...
4067  Out << I.getOpcodeName();
4068 
4069  // If this is an atomic load or store, print out the atomic marker.
4070  if ((isa<LoadInst>(I) && cast<LoadInst>(I).isAtomic()) ||
4071  (isa<StoreInst>(I) && cast<StoreInst>(I).isAtomic()))
4072  Out << " atomic";
4073 
4074  if (isa<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I) && cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I).isWeak())
4075  Out << " weak";
4076 
4077  // If this is a volatile operation, print out the volatile marker.
4078  if ((isa<LoadInst>(I) && cast<LoadInst>(I).isVolatile()) ||
4079  (isa<StoreInst>(I) && cast<StoreInst>(I).isVolatile()) ||
4080  (isa<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I) && cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I).isVolatile()) ||
4081  (isa<AtomicRMWInst>(I) && cast<AtomicRMWInst>(I).isVolatile()))
4082  Out << " volatile";
4083 
4084  // Print out optimization information.
4085  WriteOptimizationInfo(Out, &I);
4086 
4087  // Print out the compare instruction predicates
4088  if (const CmpInst *CI = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(&I))
4089  Out << ' ' << CmpInst::getPredicateName(CI->getPredicate());
4090 
4091  // Print out the atomicrmw operation
4092  if (const AtomicRMWInst *RMWI = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(&I))
4093  Out << ' ' << AtomicRMWInst::getOperationName(RMWI->getOperation());
4094 
4095  // Print out the type of the operands...
4096  const Value *Operand = I.getNumOperands() ? I.getOperand(0) : nullptr;
4097 
4098  // Special case conditional branches to swizzle the condition out to the front
4099  if (isa<BranchInst>(I) && cast<BranchInst>(I).isConditional()) {
4100  const BranchInst &BI(cast<BranchInst>(I));
4101  Out << ' ';
4102  writeOperand(BI.getCondition(), true);
4103  Out << ", ";
4104  writeOperand(BI.getSuccessor(0), true);
4105  Out << ", ";
4106  writeOperand(BI.getSuccessor(1), true);
4107 
4108  } else if (isa<SwitchInst>(I)) {
4109  const SwitchInst& SI(cast<SwitchInst>(I));
4110  // Special case switch instruction to get formatting nice and correct.
4111  Out << ' ';
4112  writeOperand(SI.getCondition(), true);
4113  Out << ", ";
4114  writeOperand(SI.getDefaultDest(), true);
4115  Out << " [";
4116  for (auto Case : SI.cases()) {
4117  Out << "\n ";
4118  writeOperand(Case.getCaseValue(), true);
4119  Out << ", ";
4120  writeOperand(Case.getCaseSuccessor(), true);
4121  }
4122  Out << "\n ]";
4123  } else if (isa<IndirectBrInst>(I)) {
4124  // Special case indirectbr instruction to get formatting nice and correct.
4125  Out << ' ';
4126  writeOperand(Operand, true);
4127  Out << ", [";
4128 
4129  for (unsigned i = 1, e = I.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
4130  if (i != 1)
4131  Out << ", ";
4132  writeOperand(I.getOperand(i), true);
4133  }
4134  Out << ']';
4135  } else if (const PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(&I)) {
4136  Out << ' ';
4137  TypePrinter.print(I.getType(), Out);
4138  Out << ' ';
4139 
4140  for (unsigned op = 0, Eop = PN->getNumIncomingValues(); op < Eop; ++op) {
4141  if (op) Out << ", ";
4142  Out << "[ ";
4143  writeOperand(PN->getIncomingValue(op), false); Out << ", ";
4144  writeOperand(PN->getIncomingBlock(op), false); Out << " ]";
4145  }
4146  } else if (const ExtractValueInst *EVI = dyn_cast<ExtractValueInst>(&I)) {
4147  Out << ' ';
4148  writeOperand(I.getOperand(0), true);
4149  for (unsigned i : EVI->indices())
4150  Out << ", " << i;
4151  } else if (const InsertValueInst *IVI = dyn_cast<InsertValueInst>(&I)) {
4152  Out << ' ';
4153  writeOperand(I.getOperand(0), true); Out << ", ";
4154  writeOperand(I.getOperand(1), true);
4155  for (unsigned i : IVI->indices())
4156  Out << ", " << i;
4157  } else if (const LandingPadInst *LPI = dyn_cast<LandingPadInst>(&I)) {
4158  Out << ' ';
4159  TypePrinter.print(I.getType(), Out);
4160  if (LPI->isCleanup() || LPI->getNumClauses() != 0)
4161  Out << '\n';
4162 
4163  if (LPI->isCleanup())
4164  Out << " cleanup";
4165 
4166  for (unsigned i = 0, e = LPI->getNumClauses(); i != e; ++i) {
4167  if (i != 0 || LPI->isCleanup()) Out << "\n";
4168  if (LPI->isCatch(i))
4169  Out << " catch ";
4170  else
4171  Out << " filter ";
4172 
4173  writeOperand(LPI->getClause(i), true);
4174  }
4175  } else if (const auto *CatchSwitch = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(&I)) {
4176  Out << " within ";
4177  writeOperand(CatchSwitch->getParentPad(), /*PrintType=*/false);
4178  Out << " [";
4179  unsigned Op = 0;
4180  for (const BasicBlock *PadBB : CatchSwitch->handlers()) {
4181  if (Op > 0)
4182  Out << ", ";
4183  writeOperand(PadBB, /*PrintType=*/true);
4184  ++Op;
4185  }
4186  Out << "] unwind ";
4187  if (const BasicBlock *UnwindDest = CatchSwitch->getUnwindDest())
4188  writeOperand(UnwindDest, /*PrintType=*/true);
4189  else
4190  Out << "to caller";
4191  } else if (const auto *FPI = dyn_cast<FuncletPadInst>(&I)) {
4192  Out << " within ";
4193  writeOperand(FPI->getParentPad(), /*PrintType=*/false);
4194  Out << " [";
4195  for (unsigned Op = 0, NumOps = FPI->arg_size(); Op < NumOps; ++Op) {
4196  if (Op > 0)
4197  Out << ", ";
4198  writeOperand(FPI->getArgOperand(Op), /*PrintType=*/true);
4199  }
4200  Out << ']';
4201  } else if (isa<ReturnInst>(I) && !Operand) {
4202  Out << " void";
4203  } else if (const auto *CRI = dyn_cast<CatchReturnInst>(&I)) {
4204  Out << " from ";
4205  writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(0), /*PrintType=*/false);
4206 
4207  Out << " to ";
4208  writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(1), /*PrintType=*/true);
4209  } else if (const auto *CRI = dyn_cast<CleanupReturnInst>(&I)) {
4210  Out << " from ";
4211  writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(0), /*PrintType=*/false);
4212 
4213  Out << " unwind ";
4214  if (CRI->hasUnwindDest())
4215  writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(1), /*PrintType=*/true);
4216  else
4217  Out << "to caller";
4218  } else if (const CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I)) {
4219  // Print the calling convention being used.
4220  if (CI->getCallingConv() != CallingConv::C) {
4221  Out << " ";
4222  PrintCallingConv(CI->getCallingConv(), Out);
4223  }
4224 
4225  Operand = CI->getCalledOperand();
4226  FunctionType *FTy = CI->getFunctionType();
4227  Type *RetTy = FTy->getReturnType();
4228  const AttributeList &PAL = CI->getAttributes();
4229 
4230  if (PAL.hasRetAttrs())
4231  Out << ' ' << PAL.getAsString(AttributeList::ReturnIndex);
4232 
4233  // Only print addrspace(N) if necessary:
4234  maybePrintCallAddrSpace(Operand, &I, Out);
4235 
4236  // If possible, print out the short form of the call instruction. We can
4237  // only do this if the first argument is a pointer to a nonvararg function,
4238  // and if the return type is not a pointer to a function.
4239  Out << ' ';
4240  TypePrinter.print(FTy->isVarArg() ? FTy : RetTy, Out);
4241  Out << ' ';
4242  writeOperand(Operand, false);
4243  Out << '(';
4244  for (unsigned op = 0, Eop = CI->arg_size(); op < Eop; ++op) {
4245  if (op > 0)
4246  Out << ", ";
4247  writeParamOperand(CI->getArgOperand(op), PAL.getParamAttrs(op));
4248  }
4249 
4250  // Emit an ellipsis if this is a musttail call in a vararg function. This
4251  // is only to aid readability, musttail calls forward varargs by default.
4252  if (CI->isMustTailCall() && CI->getParent() &&
4253  CI->getParent()->getParent() &&
4254  CI->getParent()->getParent()->isVarArg()) {
4255  if (CI->arg_size() > 0)
4256  Out << ", ";
4257  Out << "...";
4258  }
4259 
4260  Out << ')';
4261  if (PAL.hasFnAttrs())
4262  Out << " #" << Machine.getAttributeGroupSlot(PAL.getFnAttrs());
4263 
4264  writeOperandBundles(CI);
4265  } else if (const InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(&I)) {
4266  Operand = II->getCalledOperand();
4267  FunctionType *FTy = II->getFunctionType();
4268  Type *RetTy = FTy->getReturnType();
4269  const AttributeList &PAL = II->getAttributes();
4270 
4271  // Print the calling convention being used.
4272  if (II->getCallingConv() != CallingConv::C) {
4273  Out << " ";
4274  PrintCallingConv(II->getCallingConv(), Out);
4275  }
4276 
4277  if (PAL.hasRetAttrs())
4278  Out << ' ' << PAL.getAsString(AttributeList::ReturnIndex);
4279 
4280  // Only print addrspace(N) if necessary:
4281  maybePrintCallAddrSpace(Operand, &I, Out);
4282 
4283  // If possible, print out the short form of the invoke instruction. We can
4284  // only do this if the first argument is a pointer to a nonvararg function,
4285  // and if the return type is not a pointer to a function.
4286  //
4287  Out << ' ';
4288  TypePrinter.print(FTy->isVarArg() ? FTy : RetTy, Out);
4289  Out << ' ';
4290  writeOperand(Operand, false);
4291  Out << '(';
4292  for (unsigned op = 0, Eop = II->arg_size(); op < Eop; ++op) {
4293  if (op)
4294  Out << ", ";
4295  writeParamOperand(II->getArgOperand(op), PAL.getParamAttrs(op));
4296  }
4297 
4298  Out << ')';
4299  if (PAL.hasFnAttrs())
4300  Out << " #" << Machine.getAttributeGroupSlot(PAL.getFnAttrs());
4301 
4302  writeOperandBundles(II);
4303 
4304  Out << "\n to ";
4305  writeOperand(II->getNormalDest(), true);
4306  Out << " unwind ";
4307  writeOperand(II->getUnwindDest(), true);
4308  } else if (const CallBrInst *CBI = dyn_cast<CallBrInst>(&I)) {
4309  Operand = CBI->getCalledOperand();
4310  FunctionType *FTy = CBI->getFunctionType();
4311  Type *RetTy = FTy->getReturnType();
4312  const AttributeList &PAL = CBI->getAttributes();
4313 
4314  // Print the calling convention being used.
4315  if (CBI->getCallingConv() != CallingConv::C) {
4316  Out << " ";
4317  PrintCallingConv(CBI->getCallingConv(), Out);
4318  }
4319 
4320  if (PAL.hasRetAttrs())
4321  Out << ' ' << PAL.getAsString(AttributeList::ReturnIndex);
4322 
4323  // If possible, print out the short form of the callbr instruction. We can
4324  // only do this if the first argument is a pointer to a nonvararg function,
4325  // and if the return type is not a pointer to a function.
4326  //
4327  Out << ' ';
4328  TypePrinter.print(FTy->isVarArg() ? FTy : RetTy, Out);
4329  Out << ' ';
4330  writeOperand(Operand, false);
4331  Out << '(';
4332  for (unsigned op = 0, Eop = CBI->arg_size(); op < Eop; ++op) {
4333  if (op)
4334  Out << ", ";
4335  writeParamOperand(CBI->getArgOperand(op), PAL.getParamAttrs(op));
4336  }
4337 
4338  Out << ')';
4339  if (PAL.hasFnAttrs())
4340  Out << " #" << Machine.getAttributeGroupSlot(PAL.getFnAttrs());
4341 
4342  writeOperandBundles(CBI);
4343 
4344  Out << "\n to ";
4345  writeOperand(CBI->getDefaultDest(), true);
4346  Out << " [";
4347  for (unsigned i = 0, e = CBI->getNumIndirectDests(); i != e; ++i) {
4348  if (i != 0)
4349  Out << ", ";
4350  writeOperand(CBI->getIndirectDest(i), true);
4351  }
4352  Out << ']';
4353  } else if (const AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(&I)) {
4354  Out << ' ';
4355  if (AI->isUsedWithInAlloca())
4356  Out << "inalloca ";
4357  if (AI->isSwiftError())
4358  Out << "swifterror ";
4359  TypePrinter.print(AI->getAllocatedType(), Out);
4360 
4361  // Explicitly write the array size if the code is broken, if it's an array
4362  // allocation, or if the type is not canonical for scalar allocations. The
4363  // latter case prevents the type from mutating when round-tripping through
4364  // assembly.
4365  if (!AI->getArraySize() || AI->isArrayAllocation() ||
4366  !AI->getArraySize()->getType()->isIntegerTy(32)) {
4367  Out << ", ";
4368  writeOperand(AI->getArraySize(), true);
4369  }
4370  if (MaybeAlign A = AI->getAlign()) {
4371  Out << ", align " << A->value();
4372  }
4373 
4374  unsigned AddrSpace = AI->getAddressSpace();
4375  if (AddrSpace != 0) {
4376  Out << ", addrspace(" << AddrSpace << ')';
4377  }
4378  } else if (isa<CastInst>(I)) {
4379  if (Operand) {
4380  Out << ' ';
4381  writeOperand(Operand, true); // Work with broken code
4382  }
4383  Out << " to ";
4384  TypePrinter.print(I.getType(), Out);
4385  } else if (isa<VAArgInst>(I)) {
4386  if (Operand) {
4387  Out << ' ';
4388  writeOperand(Operand, true); // Work with broken code
4389  }
4390  Out << ", ";
4391  TypePrinter.print(I.getType(), Out);
4392  } else if (Operand) { // Print the normal way.
4393  if (const auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(&I)) {
4394  Out << ' ';
4395  TypePrinter.print(GEP->getSourceElementType(), Out);
4396  Out << ',';
4397  } else if (const auto *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(&I)) {
4398  Out << ' ';
4399  TypePrinter.print(LI->getType(), Out);
4400  Out << ',';
4401  }
4402 
4403  // PrintAllTypes - Instructions who have operands of all the same type
4404  // omit the type from all but the first operand. If the instruction has
4405  // different type operands (for example br), then they are all printed.
4406  bool PrintAllTypes = false;
4407  Type *TheType = Operand->getType();
4408 
4409  // Select, Store, ShuffleVector, CmpXchg and AtomicRMW always print all
4410  // types.
4411  if (isa<SelectInst>(I) || isa<StoreInst>(I) || isa<ShuffleVectorInst>(I) ||
4412  isa<ReturnInst>(I) || isa<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I) ||
4413  isa<AtomicRMWInst>(I)) {
4414  PrintAllTypes = true;
4415  } else {
4416  for (unsigned i = 1, E = I.getNumOperands(); i != E; ++i) {
4417  Operand = I.getOperand(i);
4418  // note that Operand shouldn't be null, but the test helps make dump()
4419  // more tolerant of malformed IR
4420  if (Operand && Operand->getType() != TheType) {
4421  PrintAllTypes = true; // We have differing types! Print them all!
4422  break;
4423  }
4424  }
4425  }
4426 
4427  if (!PrintAllTypes) {
4428  Out << ' ';
4429  TypePrinter.print(TheType, Out);
4430  }
4431 
4432  Out << ' ';
4433  for (unsigned i = 0, E = I.getNumOperands(); i != E; ++i) {
4434  if (i) Out << ", ";
4435  writeOperand(I.getOperand(i), PrintAllTypes);
4436  }
4437  }
4438 
4439  // Print atomic ordering/alignment for memory operations
4440  if (const LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(&I)) {
4441  if (LI->isAtomic())
4442  writeAtomic(LI->getContext(), LI->getOrdering(), LI->getSyncScopeID());
4443  if (MaybeAlign A = LI->getAlign())
4444  Out << ", align " << A->value();
4445  } else if (const StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I)) {
4446  if (SI->isAtomic())
4447  writeAtomic(SI->getContext(), SI->getOrdering(), SI->getSyncScopeID());
4448  if (MaybeAlign A = SI->getAlign())
4449  Out << ", align " << A->value();
4450  } else if (const AtomicCmpXchgInst *CXI = dyn_cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(&I)) {
4451  writeAtomicCmpXchg(CXI->getContext(), CXI->getSuccessOrdering(),
4452  CXI->getFailureOrdering(), CXI->getSyncScopeID());
4453  Out << ", align " << CXI->getAlign().value();
4454  } else if (const AtomicRMWInst *RMWI = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(&I)) {
4455  writeAtomic(RMWI->getContext(), RMWI->getOrdering(),
4456  RMWI->getSyncScopeID());
4457  Out << ", align " << RMWI->getAlign().value();
4458  } else if (const FenceInst *FI = dyn_cast<FenceInst>(&I)) {
4459  writeAtomic(FI->getContext(), FI->getOrdering(), FI->getSyncScopeID());
4460  } else if (const ShuffleVectorInst *SVI = dyn_cast<ShuffleVectorInst>(&I)) {
4461  PrintShuffleMask(Out, SVI->getType(), SVI->getShuffleMask());
4462  }
4463 
4464  // Print Metadata info.
4465  SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>, 4> InstMD;
4466  I.getAllMetadata(InstMD);
4467  printMetadataAttachments(InstMD, ", ");
4468 
4469  // Print a nice comment.
4470  printInfoComment(I);
4471 }

4473 void AssemblyWriter::printMetadataAttachments(
4474  const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>> &MDs,
4475  StringRef Separator) {
4476  if (MDs.empty())
4477  return;
4478 
4479  if (MDNames.empty())
4480  MDs[0].second->getContext().getMDKindNames(MDNames);
4481 
4482  auto WriterCtx = getContext();
4483  for (const auto &I : MDs) {
4484  unsigned Kind = I.first;
4485  Out << Separator;
4486  if (Kind < MDNames.size()) {
4487  Out << "!";
4488  printMetadataIdentifier(MDNames[Kind], Out);
4489  } else
4490  Out << "!<unknown kind #" << Kind << ">";
4491  Out << ' ';
4492  WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, I.second, WriterCtx);
4493  }
4494 }

4688 static bool isReferencingMDNode(const Instruction &I) {
4689  if (const auto *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I))
4690  if (Function *F = CI->getCalledFunction())
4691  if (F->isIntrinsic())
4692  for (auto &Op : I.operands())
4693  if (auto *V = dyn_cast_or_null<MetadataAsValue>(Op))
4694  if (isa<MDNode>(V->getMetadata()))
4695  return true;
4696  return false;
4697 }

4699 void Value::print(raw_ostream &ROS, bool IsForDebug) const {
4700  bool ShouldInitializeAllMetadata = false;
4701  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(this))
4702  ShouldInitializeAllMetadata = isReferencingMDNode(*I);
4703  else if (isa<Function>(this) || isa<MetadataAsValue>(this))
4704  ShouldInitializeAllMetadata = true;
4705 
4706  ModuleSlotTracker MST(getModuleFromVal(this), ShouldInitializeAllMetadata);
4707  print(ROS, MST, IsForDebug);
4708 }
4709 
4710 void Value::print(raw_ostream &ROS, ModuleSlotTracker &MST,
4711  bool IsForDebug) const {
4712  formatted_raw_ostream OS(ROS);
4713  SlotTracker EmptySlotTable(static_cast<const Module *>(nullptr));
4714  SlotTracker &SlotTable =
4715  MST.getMachine() ? *MST.getMachine() : EmptySlotTable;
4716  auto incorporateFunction = [&](const Function *F) {
4717  if (F)
4718  MST.incorporateFunction(*F);
4719  };
4720 
4721  if (const Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(this)) {
4722  incorporateFunction(I->getParent() ? I->getParent()->getParent() : nullptr);
4723  AssemblyWriter W(OS, SlotTable, getModuleFromVal(I), nullptr, IsForDebug);
4724  W.printInstruction(*I);
4725  } else if (const BasicBlock *BB = dyn_cast<BasicBlock>(this)) {
4726  incorporateFunction(BB->getParent());
4727  AssemblyWriter W(OS, SlotTable, getModuleFromVal(BB), nullptr, IsForDebug);
4728  W.printBasicBlock(BB);
4729  } else if (const GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(this)) {
4730  AssemblyWriter W(OS, SlotTable, GV->getParent(), nullptr, IsForDebug);
4731  if (const GlobalVariable *V = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(GV))
4732  W.printGlobal(V);
4733  else if (const Function *F = dyn_cast<Function>(GV))
4734  W.printFunction(F);
4735  else if (const GlobalAlias *A = dyn_cast<GlobalAlias>(GV))
4736  W.printAlias(A);
4737  else if (const GlobalIFunc *I = dyn_cast<GlobalIFunc>(GV))
4738  W.printIFunc(I);
4739  else
4740  llvm_unreachable("Unknown GlobalValue to print out!");
4741  } else if (const MetadataAsValue *V = dyn_cast<MetadataAsValue>(this)) {
4742  V->getMetadata()->print(ROS, MST, getModuleFromVal(V));
4743  } else if (const Constant *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(this)) {
4744  TypePrinting TypePrinter;
4745  TypePrinter.print(C->getType(), OS);
4746  OS << ' ';
4747  AsmWriterContext WriterCtx(&TypePrinter, MST.getMachine());
4748  WriteConstantInternal(OS, C, WriterCtx);
4749  } else if (isa<InlineAsm>(this) || isa<Argument>(this)) {
4750  this->printAsOperand(OS, /* PrintType */ true, MST);
4751  } else {
4752  llvm_unreachable("Unknown value to print out!");
4753  }
4754 }

4756 /// Print without a type, skipping the TypePrinting object.
4757 ///
4758 /// \return \c true iff printing was successful.
4759 static bool printWithoutType(const Value &V, raw_ostream &O,
4760  SlotTracker *Machine, const Module *M) {
4761  if (V.hasName() || isa<GlobalValue>(V) ||
4762  (!isa<Constant>(V) && !isa<MetadataAsValue>(V))) {
4763  AsmWriterContext WriterCtx(nullptr, Machine, M);
4764  WriteAsOperandInternal(O, &V, WriterCtx);
4765  return true;
4766  }
4767  return false;
4768 }

4770 static void printAsOperandImpl(const Value &V, raw_ostream &O, bool PrintType,
4771  ModuleSlotTracker &MST) {
4772  TypePrinting TypePrinter(MST.getModule());
4773  if (PrintType) {
4774  TypePrinter.print(V.getType(), O);
4775  O << ' ';
4776  }
4777 
4778  AsmWriterContext WriterCtx(&TypePrinter, MST.getMachine(), MST.getModule());
4779  WriteAsOperandInternal(O, &V, WriterCtx);
4780 }

4782 void Value::printAsOperand(raw_ostream &O, bool PrintType,
4783  const Module *M) const {
4784  if (!M)
4785  M = getModuleFromVal(this);
4786 
4787  if (!PrintType)
4788  if (printWithoutType(*this, O, nullptr, M))
4789  return;
4790 
4791  SlotTracker Machine(
4792  M, /* ShouldInitializeAllMetadata */ isa<MetadataAsValue>(this));
4793  ModuleSlotTracker MST(Machine, M);
4794  printAsOperandImpl(*this, O, PrintType, MST);
4795 }
4796 
4797 void Value::printAsOperand(raw_ostream &O, bool PrintType,
4798  ModuleSlotTracker &MST) const {
4799  if (!PrintType)
4800  if (printWithoutType(*this, O, MST.getMachine(), MST.getModule()))
4801  return;
4802 
4803  printAsOperandImpl(*this, O, PrintType, MST);
4804 }

4806 /// Recursive version of printMetadataImpl.
4807 static void printMetadataImplRec(raw_ostream &ROS, const Metadata &MD,
4808  AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx) {
4809  formatted_raw_ostream OS(ROS);
4810  WriteAsOperandInternal(OS, &MD, WriterCtx, /* FromValue */ true);
4811 
4812  auto *N = dyn_cast<MDNode>(&MD);
4813  if (!N || isa<DIExpression>(MD) || isa<DIArgList>(MD))
4814  return;
4815 
4816  OS << " = ";
4817  WriteMDNodeBodyInternal(OS, N, WriterCtx);
4818 }

4820 namespace {
4821 struct MDTreeAsmWriterContext : public AsmWriterContext {
4822  unsigned Level;
4823  // {Level, Printed string}
4824  using EntryTy = std::pair<unsigned, std::string>;
4825  SmallVector<EntryTy, 4> Buffer;
4826 
4827  // Used to break the cycle in case there is any.
4828  SmallPtrSet<const Metadata *, 4> Visited;
4829 
4830  raw_ostream &MainOS;
4831 
4832  MDTreeAsmWriterContext(TypePrinting *TP, SlotTracker *ST, const Module *M,
4833  raw_ostream &OS, const Metadata *InitMD)
4834  : AsmWriterContext(TP, ST, M), Level(0U), Visited({InitMD}), MainOS(OS) {}
4835 
4836  void onWriteMetadataAsOperand(const Metadata *MD) override {
4837  if (!Visited.insert(MD).second)
4838  return;
4839 
4840  std::string Str;
4841  raw_string_ostream SS(Str);
4842  ++Level;
4843  // A placeholder entry to memorize the correct
4844  // position in buffer.
4845  Buffer.emplace_back(std::make_pair(Level, ""));
4846  unsigned InsertIdx = Buffer.size() - 1;
4847 
4848  printMetadataImplRec(SS, *MD, *this);
4849  Buffer[InsertIdx].second = std::move(SS.str());
4850  --Level;
4851  }
4852 
4853  ~MDTreeAsmWriterContext() {
4854  for (const auto &Entry : Buffer) {
4855  MainOS << "\n";
4856  unsigned NumIndent = Entry.first * 2U;
4857  MainOS.indent(NumIndent) << Entry.second;
4858  }
4859  }
4860 };
4861 } // end anonymous namespace
4862 
4863 static void printMetadataImpl(raw_ostream &ROS, const Metadata &MD,
4864  ModuleSlotTracker &MST, const Module *M,
4865  bool OnlyAsOperand, bool PrintAsTree = false) {
4866  formatted_raw_ostream OS(ROS);
4867 
4868  TypePrinting TypePrinter(M);
4869 
4870  std::unique_ptr<AsmWriterContext> WriterCtx;
4871  if (PrintAsTree && !OnlyAsOperand)
4872  WriterCtx = std::make_unique<MDTreeAsmWriterContext>(
4873  &TypePrinter, MST.getMachine(), M, OS, &MD);
4874  else
4875  WriterCtx =
4876  std::make_unique<AsmWriterContext>(&TypePrinter, MST.getMachine(), M);
4877 
4878  WriteAsOperandInternal(OS, &MD, *WriterCtx, /* FromValue */ true);
4879 
4880  auto *N = dyn_cast<MDNode>(&MD);
4881  if (OnlyAsOperand || !N || isa<DIExpression>(MD) || isa<DIArgList>(MD))
4882  return;
4883 
4884  OS << " = ";
4885  WriteMDNodeBodyInternal(OS, N, *WriterCtx);
4886 }

4891 }

4928 void ModuleSlotTracker::collectMDNodes(MachineMDNodeListType &L, unsigned LB,
4929  unsigned UB) const {
4930  SlotTracker *ST = MachineStorage.get();
4931  if (!ST)
4932  return;
4933 
4934  for (auto &I : llvm::make_range(ST->mdn_begin(), ST->mdn_end()))
4935  if (I.second >= LB && I.second < UB)
4936  L.push_back(std::make_pair(I.second, I.first));
4937 }
